[ti:I Loved You In Silence]
[ar:Srijan Dwivedi]
[length:04:33]

[00:00.00][Verse 1]
[00:00.00]I learned your laugh like a prayer in the dark
[00:18.50]Memorized every piece of your heart
[00:20.96]You were sunlight falling on me
[00:24.74]But I was never the one you could see
[00:27.88]I stayed where your shadow would fall
[00:31.20]Built my world around someone so small
[00:34.82]You were living a life without me
[00:38.36]While you were everything I could be
[00:42.30]You never heard the words I couldn't say
[00:46.14]They drowned inside my chest each day
[00:49.62]I was a ghost inside your light
[00:53.16]Watching you disappear every night
[00:57.94]You never loved me, not even close
[01:01.60]I was the secret nobody knows
[01:05.02]You were the heaven I couldn’t reach
[01:08.42]A silent prayer I couldn’t preach
[01:11.68]I broke in places you couldn’t see
[01:15.24]You kept the air I needed to breathe
[01:18.72]You walked away without a sound
[01:22.14]And left my whole world burning down
[01:25.64]You never loved me
[01:31.12]But you were all I ever had
[01:37.82]Every night your name in my head
[01:44.20]Echoes louder inside my bed
[01:46.68]Every dream ends the same old way
[01:50.00]You turning slowly and walking away
[01:53.14]I tried to bury the love I kept
[01:56.86]But even silence remembers you best
[01:59.94]Your memory lives under my skin
[02:03.86]Like a scar I can’t hide within
[02:07.78][Pre-Chorus]
[02:07.78]You held my heart like it weighed nothing
[02:11.84]Like breaking it meant nothing
[02:15.06]While I was drowning in the sea
[02:18.88]Of someone you’d never be
[02:23.68]You never loved me, not even close
[02:27.34]I was the secret nobody knows
[02:30.72]You were the heaven I couldn’t reach
[02:34.12]A silent prayer I couldn’t preach
[02:37.42]I broke in places you couldn’t see
[02:40.96]You kept the air I needed to breathe
[02:44.42]You walked away without a sound
[02:47.86]And left my whole world burning down
[02:51.66][Verse 2]
[02:51.66]Sometimes I wonder
[02:53.54]If my name ever crossed your mind
[02:55.34]If for a second
[03:01.98]You felt the love that ruined mine
[03:08.42]Because loving you
[03:14.20]Was the slowest way to die
[03:18.54]You never loved me, not even once
[03:21.92]But I gave you everything I was
[03:25.58]You were the light I couldn’t hold
[03:29.02]A beautiful lie I never told
[03:32.22]Now every night I lie awake
[03:35.86]With all the pieces that you break
[03:39.28]You never stayed, you never tried
[03:42.70]But somehow you still live inside
[03:46.10]You never loved me
[03:51.08]But I loved you until it hurt to breathe
[03:57.30]And if one day you hear this song
[04:00.72]And wonder who it’s written for
[04:03.82]Just remember
[04:07.32]There was someone
[04:09.08]Who loved you quietly
[04:14.40]Enough to destroy himself.